        "TECTIBRANCHIATA": "An order, or suborder, of gastropod Mollusca in which the gillsare usually situated on one side of the back, and protected by a foldof the mantle. When there is a shell, it is usually thin and delicateand often rudimentary. The aplysias and the bubble shells areexamples.",
        "TECTIBRANCHIATE": "Having the gills covered by the mantle; of or pertaining to theTectibranchiata.-- n.",
