        "TELEOZOIC": "Having tissued composed of cells.",
        "TELEPATHY": "The sympathetic affection of one mind by the thoughts,feelings, or emotions of another at a distance, without communicationthrough the ordinary channels of sensation.-- Tel`e*path\"ic, a.-- Te*lep\"a*thist, n.",
        "TELEPHEME": "A message by a telephone. [Recent]",
        "TELEPHONE": "An instrument for reproducing sounds, especially articulatespeech, at a distance.",
