        "TENE": "See 1st and 2d Teen. [Obs.]",
        "TENEBRAE": "The matins and lauds for the last three days of Holy Week,commemorating the sufferings and death of Christ, -- usually sung onthe afternoon or evening of Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday, insteadof on the following days.",
        "TENEBRICOSE": "Tenebrous; dark; gloomy. [Obs.]",
        "TENEBRIFIC": "Rendering dark or gloomy; tenebrous; gloomy.It lightens, it brightens, The tenebrific scene. Burns.Where light Lay fitful in a tenebrific time. R. Browning.",
        "TENEBRIFICOUS": "Tenebrific.Authors who are tenebrificous stars. Addison.",
