        "THERAPY": "Therapeutics.",
        "THERE-ANENT": "Concerning that. [Scot.]",
        "THEREAGAIN": "In opposition; against one's course. [Obs.]If that him list to stand thereagain. Chaucer.",
        "THEREAT": "Before that time; beforehand. [Obs.]Many a winter therebiforn. Chaucer.",
        "THEREFOR": "For that, or this; for it.With certain officers ordained therefore. Chaucer.",
        "THEREFROM": "From this or that.Turn not aside therefrom to the right hand or to the left. John.xxiii. 6.",
        "THEREIN": "In that or this place, time, or thing; in that particular orrespect. Wyclif.He pricketh through a fair forest, Therein is many a wild beast.Chaucer.Bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply therein. Gen. ix.7.Therein our letters do not well agree. Shak.",
        "THEREINTO": "Into that or this, or into that place. Bacon.Let not them . . . enter thereinto. Luke xxi. 21.",
        "THEREOF": "Of that or this.In the day that thou eatest thereof, thou shalt surely die. Gen. ii.17.",
        "THEREOLOGY": "Therapeutios.",
        "THEREON": "On that or this. Chaucer.Then the king said, Hang him thereon. Esther vii. 9.",
