        "THIMBLE": "Any thimble-shaped appendage or fixure. Specifically: --(a) A tubular piece, generally a strut, through which a bolt or pinpasses.(b) A fixed or movable ring, tube, or lining placed in a hole.(c) A tubular cone for expanding a flue; -- called ferrule inEngland.",
