        "TOLLAGE": "Payment of toll; also, the amount or quantity paid as toll.Drayton.",
        "TOLLBOOTH": "To imprison in a tollbooth. [R.]That they might tollbooth Oxford men. Bp. Corbet.",
        "TOLLER": "A toll gatherer. \"Tollers in markets.\" Piers Plowman.",
        "TOLLETANE": "Of or pertaining to Toledo in Spain; made in Toledo. [Obs.]\"Tables Tolletanes.\" Chaucer.",
