        "TONOPHANT": "A modification of the kaleidophon, for showing composition ofacoustic vibrations. It consists of two thin slips of steel weldedtogether, their length being adjystable by a screw socket.",
        "TONOUS": "Abounding in tone or sound.",
        "TONQUIN BEAN": "See Tonka bean.",
        "TONSIL": "One of the two glandular organs situated in the throat at thesides of the fauces. The tonsils are sometimes called the almonds,from their shape.",
