        "TOPEK": "An ESkimo house made of material other than snow, esp. onehaving walls of turf, driftwood, rock, or skin, and a roof of skinsof the walrus or seal. In Alaska it is often partially undergroundand covered with timber and turf. Topeks are also used by Indians ofthe lower Yukon region.",
