        "TOPONYM": "A name of a place; more broadly, a name, as in the binomialname of a plant, based on, or derived from, a place name, or based onthe location of the thing named.",
        "TOPONYMY": "A system of toponyms; the use of toponyms. -- To*pon\"y*mal (#),Top`o*nym\"ic (#), Top`o*nym\"ic*al (#), a.",
        "TOPOPHONE": "A double ear trumpet for estimating the direction from whichsounds proceed, esp. for the use of navigators.",
