        "TRACTRIX": "A curve such that the part of the tangent between the point oftangency and a given straight line is constant; -- so called becauseit was conceived as described by the motion of one end of a tangentline as the other end was drawn along the given line.",
        "TRAD": "imp. of Tread. Chaucer.",
        "TRADE": "The trade winds.",
        "TRADE-MARK": "A peculiar distinguishing mark or device affixed by amanufacturer or a merchant to his goods, the exclusive right of usingwhich is recognized by law.",
        "TRADED": "Professional; practiced. [Obs.] Shak.",
        "TRADEFUL": "Full of trade; busy in traffic; commercial. Spenser.",
        "TRADELESS": "Having no trade or traffic. Young.",
