        "TRADESWOMAN": "A woman who trades, or is skilled in trade.",
        "TRADITION": "To transmit by way of tradition; to hand down. [Obs.]The following story is . . . traditioned with very much creditamongst our English Catholics. Fuller.",
        "TRADITIONALISM": "A system of faith founded on tradition; esp., the doctrine thatall religious faith is to be based solely upon what is delivered fromcompetent authority, exclusive of rational processes.",
