        "TUNGSTEN": "A rare element of the chromium group found in certain minerals,as wolfram and scheelite, and isolated as a heavy steel-gray metalwhich is very hard and infusible. It has both acid and basicproperties. When alloyed in small quantities with steel, it greatlyincreases its hardness. Symbol W (Wolframium). Atomic weight, 183.6.Specific gravity, 18.",
        "TUNGSTEN LAMP": "An electric glow lamp having filaments of metallic tungsten.Such lamps, owing to the refractory nature of the metal, may bemaintained at a very high temperature and require an expenditure ofonly about 1.25 watts per candle power.",
